1.	Center for Continuous Electoral Training improved capacities, developed at least 10 new  training curricula, methodologies and materials, as well as increased the pool of professional trainers (with at least 20); 
1.1.	The E-Learning Platform is upgraded and functional, and populated with at least 20 training modules;  
2.	Expertise in the area of electoral system provided. Alternative voting channel (electronic voting) to improve electoral system identified and analyzed; 
Set of amendments to the Electoral legislation developed; 
2.1	New concept approved by Civil Status Service and facilitation of dialog and consultations with stakeholders provided; 
3.	CEC is fully capable to monitor and manage the political parties financing.
Regulations and reporting tools are in place. Expertise in developing IT module provided.
4.	State Register of Voters  improved through more aligned functionalities and interconnected within the State Automated Information System  Elections with at least 2 new modules; 
4.1. Legal and regulatory framework of the address system developed. IT system of the address register modernized. 
4.2.   The interoperability with the State Register of Voters of at least 2 key-state registers fully established.

1.	Target achieved. Center for Continuous Electoral Training demonstrated strong capacities of delivering training for 8,072 electoral officials for unplanned Presidential Elections; portfolio improved with 17 new training curricula, methodologies and materials; the pool of professional trainers increased with 50 persons. 
1.1.	The E-Learning Platform is upgraded and functional and populated with  27 training modules;
2.	Target achieved. Expertise in electoral reform successfully provided. Alternative voting channel identified and analyzed through a feasibility study. Facilitation of dialog and consultations with Civil Society Organizations and general public on the internet voting fully ensured through 3 public events; Legal expertise on improving electoral legislation on internet voting introduction consistently provided; Set of amendments to the Electoral legislation developed;
2.1	100% achieved new  concept approved by Civil Status Service and facilitation of dialog and consultations with stakeholders regularly ensured; 
3.	Target 80% achieved. Capacities to monitor and manage the political parties financing are improved through 4 trainings. Set of regulations and tools used for reporting process developed and fully implemented. Expertise in developing technical specifications
of the IT module provided; The IT module development postponed due to Presidential Elections.
4.  Target fully archived. The State Register of Voters is improved with new modern functionalities and interconnected within the State Automated Information System  Elections with 3 new modules; 
4.1. Target achieved. Legal and regulatory framework on the new address system fully developed and successfully consulted with all line-ministries. New IT system of the address register commissioned. 
4.2. Fully achieved. (1) The interoperability of the State Register of Voters with Register from the Penitentiary Dept. of the Ministry of Justice is established, piloted and functional.  (2) The interope

